For the #DiorCouture Spring Summer 2020 show we involved @Chanakya.School, an embroidery school in India supported by Dior, to create the exceptional embroidered banners designed by @Judy.Chicago. 
The school works towards empowering female students in a country where embroidery is traditionally a man’s domain.

#WeShouldAllBeFeminists

My mother dressed me in Tyrolese outfits for years, no wonder I grew up to be a designer, at least I could pick my outfits! 
On this rare palindrome day, 02022020, I turn 56!

Each one of my collections puts in discussion the themes of feminism and femininity. 
Just like in my past shows, I have chosen to collaborate with a female artist. This time, @judy.chicago created the space for my latest haute couture show with © "What if Women Ruled the World?”. #DiorCouture Spring Summer 2020
#WeShouldAllBeFeminists

The #DiorCouture Spring-Summer 2020 collection draws inspiration from the female divinities of the past, in order to promote the idea of feminine creativity. 
By celebrating women’s generative power through the ages and across a variety of cultures, it aims to support an alternative narrative. 
Womanhood is not limited to motherhood: it is a fundamental aspect, but the goddess figure also thrives through its other creative powers and abilities.

#DiorCouture Spring Summer 2020
#WeShouldAllBeFeminists

All the pieces in my collection are inspired by the peplum, a garment that becomes an impalpable aura of the women of our time. 
Each piece has its own declination, in this one I added a cape of golden feathers worthy of the Greek goddess Athena.

#DiorCouture Spring Summer 2020
#WeShouldAllBeFeminists

I chose to strengthen the concept of the goddess by using elements of nature and inserting gold as a symbol of veneration. 
#DiorCouture Spring Summer 2020
#WeShouldAllBeFeminists

©️ “What If Women Ruled The World?” is the question that @judy.chicago asked during our collaboration for the #DiorCouture Spring Summer 2020 show. 
This generated a series of new questions, asking which limits a woman would have and what the world could become.

How would you answer the question?

#WeShouldAllBeFeminists

Everytime a show is complete I like to remember all the smaller fragments that led up to the bigger picture.

@katy.hessel has been running the instagram page @thegreatwomenartists for over 4 years, a page which celebrates women artists and their work. 
I met her during the Dior Haute Couture 2020 fashion show to talk about how the idea for the show was born with @judy.chicago, as well as how the concept of the collection came to be.
